Description: The South West Highway between Greenbushes and Bunbury has become a conveyorbelt for the Tailison Lithum mine in Greenbushses. And the number of tandem trucks that travel on the road will more than trebel once the mine upgrade is complete. This is going to make the road even more unsafe. Yet there is a rail line that remains unsused, running beside the road. Upgrade the rail and get the trucks off the road.
